HEADWORD: Suberin
<hw>Su"ber*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>suber</ets>
the cork tree: cf. F. <ets>sub⟦eacute⟧rine</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A material found in the cell walls of cork. It is
a modification of lignin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

